                TIME_SLOT_REF1="ts2" TIME_SLOT_REF2="ts3">
                <ANNOTATION_VALUE>So, I have some programs prepared for today's lecture and the one of them, since the publishing of K&amp;R, is "Hello World!", but only on C++. And now we'll examine it. Let's see how bright it is. (Into the room) Do you see it? I'll scale it a little bit. Ahhh! What do we see? When in Python in order to print "Hello World!" we write just one line of code, here we have lots of fun. #include &lt;iostream&gt; (hash include iostream) . Generally speaking, the import of input-output stream library is the processing of inputs and outputs via streams. I did "int main" function in Python because it was convenient for me and I often summoned it. Here in C++ it is necessary to create the Main function but you have an opportunity NOT to summon it. Main function is the exact entry to the program. Actually, there can be a lot of functions. Yes, here I have just one but, generally speaking,</ANNOTATION_VALUE>
